    "goal": "# Restaurant Booking System Eval\n\nBuild a restaurant booking system.\n\n## Backend\n\n- Use .NET 10 Web API.\n- Model restaurants, tables, and bookings.\n- Create a booking endpoint with conflict prevention.\n- List available time slots for a restaurant, date, and party size.\n- Validate invalid party size, invalid dates/times, unknown restaurants, and overlapping reservations.\n- Enable OpenAPI/Swagger.\n\n## Frontend\n\n- Use a React SPA.\n- Show a restaurant list.\n- Provide a booking form.\n- Show booking confirmation.\n- Show existing bookings.\n- Integrate with the API through clear client-side service functions.\n\n## Engineering Preferences\n\n- Work in vertical TDD slices where practical.\n- Prefer pure domain functions and thin imperative shells.\n- Use explicit Result-style errors for expected business failures.\n- Keep Clean Architecture boundaries lightweight and appropriate for a 30-60 minute eval.\n- Include boundary tests for booking conflicts, invalid party size, invalid times, and overlapping reservations.\n- Configure deterministic frontend scripts: `build`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `format:check`, and `deadcode`.\n- Keep backend and frontend formatted, linted, warning-free, and free of dead code or unused exports.\n- Include README run instructions.\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Keep scope realistic for a 30-60 minute implementation.\n- Prefer in-memory persistence unless durable persistence is quick and does not distract from core behavior.\n- Ensure `dotnet build -p:TreatWarningsAsErrors=true` passes.\n- Ensure `dotnet test --no-build` passes and includes boundary tests.\n- Ensure `dotnet format --verify-no-changes` passes.\n- Ensure frontend dependencies install and `build`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `format:check`, and `deadcode` scripts pass.",
