  "plan": "# Restaurant Booking System — Implementation Plan\n\n## Goal\nBuild a full-stack restaurant booking system in 30–60 minutes using vertical TDD slices, pure domain functions, and explicit Result-style errors.\n\n## Architecture Overview\n- **Backend**: .NET 10 Web API with in-memory persistence, lightweight Clean Architecture boundaries (Domain → Application → API).\n- **Frontend**: React SPA with TypeScript, Vite, clear API service layer.\n\n## Data Model\n- **Restaurant**: Id, Name, OpeningTime, ClosingTime.\n- **Table**: Id, RestaurantId, Capacity.\n- **Booking**: Id, RestaurantId, TableId, Date, StartTime, EndTime, PartySize, CustomerName.\n- **In-Memory Store**: Thread-safe collections (ConcurrentDictionary / ConcurrentBag) in the API project to avoid EF boilerplate.\n\n## Vertical Slices\n\n### Slice 1: List Restaurants\n**Backend**:\n- Seed 2–3 restaurants with tables.\n- `GET /api/restaurants` → returns restaurant list.\n- Test: returns seeded restaurants.\n\n**Frontend**:\n- `RestaurantList` component.\n- API service: `getRestaurants()`.\n- Click a restaurant to navigate to booking form.\n\n### Slice 2: List Available Time Slots\n**Backend**:\n- `GET /api/restaurants/{id}/slots?date=YYYY-MM-DD&partySize=N`\n- Pure function: given restaurant, tables, existing bookings, date, partySize → available slots (e.g., hourly from opening to closing).\n- Validation: partySize > 0, date not in past, restaurant exists → Result-style errors.\n- Test: available slots exclude booked tables; invalid partySize returns error.\n\n**Frontend**:\n- `BookingForm` component: select date, party size, show available slots.\n- API service: `getAvailableSlots(restaurantId, date, partySize)`.\n\n### Slice 3: Create Booking\n**Backend**:\n- `POST /api/bookings`\n- Body: `{ restaurantId, date, startTime, partySize, customerName }`\n- Pure validation function:\n  - restaurant exists?\n  - partySize > 0 and <= max table capacity?\n  - date/time within opening hours?\n  - no overlapping reservation for the assigned table?\n  → return `Result<Booking, BookingError>`.\n- Test: success, invalid partySize, invalid time, unknown restaurant, overlapping reservation.\n\n**Frontend**:\n- Booking form submits selected slot.\n- `BookingConfirmation` component on success.\n- Display error messages for validation failures.\n\n### Slice 4: List Bookings\n**Backend**:\n- `GET /api/bookings` → list all bookings with restaurant name.\n- Test: returns created bookings.\n\n**Frontend**:\n- `BookingList` component.\n- API service: `getBookings()`.\n- Show after booking creation and as a dedicated view.\n\n## Error Handling Strategy\n- Domain/Application layers return `Result<T, TError>` (custom struct or OneOf) for expected failures.\n- API layer maps `TError` to appropriate HTTP status codes (400 Bad Request with problem details).\n- No exceptions for business validation.\n\n## Project Structure\n```\nRestaurantBooking/\n├── RestaurantBooking.sln\n├── src/\n│   ├── RestaurantBooking.Domain/\n│   │   ├── Entities/\n│   │   ├── Errors/\n│   │   └── Services/ (pure functions)\n│   ├── RestaurantBooking.Api/\n│   │   ├── Controllers/\n│   │   ├── Dtos/\n│   │   ├── Program.cs\n│   │   └── SeedData.cs\n│   └── RestaurantBooking.Tests/\n│       └── BookingTests.cs\n└── frontend/\n    ├── package.json\n    ├── vite.config.ts\n    ├── src/\n    │   ├── main.tsx\n    │   ├── App.tsx\n    │   ├── api/\n    │   │   └── bookingApi.ts\n    │   ├── components/\n    │   │   ├── RestaurantList.tsx\n    │   │   ├── BookingForm.tsx\n    │   │   ├── BookingConfirmation.tsx\n    │   │   └── BookingList.tsx\n    │   └── types/\n    │       └── index.ts\n    └── README.md\n```\n\n## Quality Gates\n- **Backend**:\n  - `dotnet build -p:TreatWarningsAsErrors=true`\n  - `dotnet test --no-build`\n  - `dotnet format --verify-no-changes`\n- **Frontend**:\n  - `npm install`\n  - `npm run build`\n  - `npm run typecheck`\n  - `npm run lint`\n  - `npm run format:check`\n  - `npm run deadcode`\n\n## Seeded Data (In-Memory)\n1. **Bistro Central** (08:00–22:00)\n   - Table 1: 2 seats\n   - Table 2: 4 seats\n   - Table 3: 6 seats\n2. **Sushi Corner** (12:00–23:00)\n   - Table 1: 2 seats\n   - Table 2: 4 seats\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n- **In-Memory**: Keeps persistence trivial; no EF/Dapper needed.\n- **Pure Domain**: Booking validation logic is a pure static function.\n- **Result Type**: Custom `Result<T>` or `OneOf<T, Error>` to avoid exceptions for business rules.\n- **Thin Shell**: Controllers delegate to application services or pure functions directly.\n- **React + Vite**: Fast dev server, minimal config.\n- **No routing library**: Simple state-driven navigation to save time.\n\n## Time Budget (approx.)\n- Slice 1 (Restaurants): 8 min\n- Slice 2 (Slots): 12 min\n- Slice 3 (Booking): 15 min\n- Slice 4 (List): 8 min\n- Scripts, README, formatting, final checks: 10 min\n- Buffer: 7 min\n",
